700068f-a.title: Bronx: 138th Street (East) - Exterior Street
700068f-a.text:
(1)
E. 138th Street, south side, east from Exterior Street to
Grand Concourse, showing clearance activities being conducted
by the Works Progress Administration for the erection of a
trailer camp for the 'merican Segion -onwention of 1937. In
the background is visible the ramp of the New York Central
Railroad.
Aumust 31, 1937

700067f-a.title: Bronx: 138th Street (East) - Exterior Street
700067f-a.text:
E. 138th Street, south side, at Exterior Street. The site
in the foreground, is part of the area which the W.P.A. built
up as a trailer ca p for the convention of the American Legion
in 1937. The view is southwestward across Exterior Street and
shows the N.Y.State Canal Terminal and bridges (left) spanning
the Barlem River.
Sept.14,1937
W.P.A.Photo
Five Boroughs 'roject
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE
(2)
Another section of the trailer camp near the New York Central
Railroad tracks.
Sept. 29, 1937
W.P.A. Photo
Five Boroughs Vroject
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE
